=begin
Write a method that takes one argument, a positive integer, and returns a list of the digits in the number.

Examples:

puts digit_list(12345) == [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]     # => true
puts digit_list(7) == [7]                     # => true
puts digit_list(375290) == [3, 7, 5, 2, 9, 0] # => true
puts digit_list(444) == [4, 4, 4]             # => true

input - positive integer
output - list of all the digits in that number
rules - method only takes one argument(positive integer) and splits all the digits in the arugment into a an array, where each letter is a separate item in an array

=end

def digit_list(number)
  number.to_s.chars.map(&:to_i)
end



